<Layout title="Yacht Crew Mortgages · FL Chief Stew + Stew + Deckhand + Bosun + Multi-Role Charter Crew Qualifying" description="Florida yacht crew mortgage sub-page covering five practice categories: Chief Stewardess / Purser senior interior management with substantial tips income; Stewardess / Steward mid-level interior; Deckhand entry-to-mid deck position with STCW basic safety plus RYA Powerboat L2; Bosun senior deck position with sometimes MCA OOW Yachts; Multi-Role Charter Crew on smaller crewed charter vessels covering deck plus interior plus sometimes engineering. MCA Maritime and Coastguard Agency STCW Standards of Training Certification and Watchkeeping. USCG Merchant Mariner Credential MMC. IMO International Maritime Organization. Foreign-flagged vessel employment (Cayman Bermuda Marshall Islands Bahamas). Multi-source mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 W-2 plus tips with 24-month averaging (U.S.-flagged). B3-3.2-01 self-employed for 1099 crew agency contract. Bank Statement Non-QM 12-24 months bank deposits for foreign-flagged vessel crew without traditional U.S. W-2. B3-6-05 student loan treatment. IRC Section 911 Foreign Earned Income Exclusion FEIE shielding up to $126K (2024 indexed) foreign earned income from U.S. federal tax for qualifying crew meeting physical presence or bona fide residence tests. IRS Form 2555 election. Conventional Conforming. Conventional Jumbo. P&L Statement Non-QM. Asset-Depletion Non-QM. DSCR Non-QM investor. FHA Conforming. VA Conforming. Cash-Out Refinance. South Florida superyacht capital. Fort Lauderdale Yachting Capital of the World. Mediterranean summer plus Caribbean winter charter pattern. Tips income substantial 10-15% of charter rate. Live-aboard accommodation eliminating rent / utilities / food expense. Florida no state income tax substantial qualifying advantage." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/yacht-professionals/yacht-crew/">
  <div class="yacht-crew-scope" set:html={yachtCrewBody} />

<HomeReviews />
</Layout>

